// Semantic direction:
// krypto_primitiver implement foundational cryptographic building blocks.
// krypto_konstant_tid ensures operations take the same time regardless of secret values.
// chacha20 is a stream cipher: XOR plaintext with a pseudorandom keystream.
// cc20_kvart_runde applies four ARX (add-rotate-XOR) operations to a 4-word column.
// poly1305 is a one-time MAC; combined with cc20 it forms an AEAD scheme.
// p1305_nøkkelklamp forces certain bits to zero to ensure correct field arithmetic.
// chacha20_poly1305 (AEAD) encrypts with cc20 and authenticates both ciphertext and cp_aad.
// aes_ni uses x86/ARM hardware instructions for constant-time, fast AES rounds.
// aes_gcm combines AES-CTR encryption with GHASH authentication for an AEAD mode.
// ghash operates in GF(2^128); it is vulnerable to nonce reuse — each gcm_iv must be unique.
// sha3_256 uses the Keccak sponge: sponge_absorber takes input; sponge_squeeze produces output.
// keccak_permutasjon applies 24 rounds of theta/rho/pi/chi/iota to a 1600-bit keccak_state.
// blake3 is faster than SHA-3; b3_tre_hashing enables parallelism across b3_chunknode inputs.
// hkdf_extract distills entropy from hkdf_ikm into a pseudorandom key; hkdf_expand derives keys.
// x25519 is Diffie-Hellman on Curve25519; montgomery_ladder prevents timing side channels.
// ed25519 signs with Edwards curves; ed25519_signer uses the private key + message hash.
// argon2id is the recommended password hashing function: memory-hard and side-channel resistant.

// Primitive flow:
// ChaCha20-Poly1305 kryptering:
//   generer engangs poly1305_nøkkel: cc20_blokk(nøkkel, nonce, counter=0)[0:32]
//   krypter: cc20_krypter(nøkkel, nonce, counter=1, ren_tekst) -> chiffertekst
//   autentiser: p1305_generer(poly_nøkkel, aad || chiffertekst) -> tag
//   send: nonce + chiffertekst + tag
// HKDF-SHA256: extract(salt, ikm) -> PRK via HMAC-SHA256
//   expand(PRK, info, L): T(1)=HMAC(PRK, ""||info||0x01), T(2)=HMAC(PRK, T(1)||info||0x02)
//   output = T(1)||T(2)||... til L bytes
// Argon2id: hash(passord, salt, m=65536 KiB, t=3, p=4)
//   fylt minneblokker -> uavhengige tråder blander -> XOR finaler -> hash

// This defines cryptographic primitives: ChaCha20-Poly1305 AEAD, AES-GCM, SHA3/Keccak
// sponge, BLAKE3 tree hashing, HKDF key derivation, X25519/Ed25519 elliptic curves,
// and Argon2id password hashing.
